This software is made available under a dual-licensing model:

1. OPEN SOURCE LICENSE (AGPL-3.0)
   For individuals, researchers, educational institutions, non-profits,
   and organizations willing to comply with AGPL-3.0 copyleft requirements.

2. COMMERCIAL LICENSE
   For organizations that cannot or do not wish to comply with AGPL-3.0,
   or that meet the Commercial License Requirement thresholds defined herein.

Additionally, ALL use of this software is subject to the ETHICAL USE POLICY
set forth in ETHICAL_USE_POLICY.md, which prohibits use in connection with
genetic use restriction technologies (GURTs), terminator seeds, and related
technologies.

================================================================================
                    SECTION 1: DEFINITIONS
================================================================================

"Software" means Bijmantra, including all source code, object code,
documentation, configuration files, assets, and associated materials
contained in this repository and any official distributions.

"Licensor" means Denish Dholaria and his successors and assigns.

"You" (or "Your") means the individual or Legal Entity exercising
permissions granted by this License.

"Legal Entity" means the union of the acting entity and all other entities
that control, are controlled by, or are under common control with that
entity. "Control" means (i) the power to direct the affairs of such entity,
or (ii) ownership of fifty percent (50%) or more of the outstanding shares
or beneficial ownership of such entity.

"Commercial Use" means any use of the Software where:
  (a) The Software or access thereto is sold, licensed for a fee, or
      otherwise commercially distributed; or
  (b) The Software is used to provide paid services to third parties; or
  (c) The Software is bundled with or incorporated into products or
      services that are sold or licensed for a fee.

"Network Use" means making the functionality of the Software available to
third parties over a computer network, including but not limited to use as
a software-as-a-service (SaaS), platform-as-a-service (PaaS), or any hosted
or cloud-based offering.

"Derivative Work" means any work that is based on or derived from the
Software, including any modification, enhancement, translation, abridgment,
condensation, expansion, or any other form in which the Software may be
recast, transformed, or adapted.

"Annual Revenue" means the total gross revenue of a Legal Entity and all
its Affiliates during the most recently completed fiscal year, calculated
in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles.

"For-Profit Agricultural Enterprise" means any Legal Entity engaged in
commercial seed production, seed sales, crop breeding for profit,
agricultural biotechnology, agrochemicals, or related agribusiness
activities.

