================================================================================
                    SECTION 3: COMMERCIAL LICENSE REQUIREMENT
================================================================================

Notwithstanding the Open Source License Grant in Section 2, a Commercial
License is REQUIRED in the following circumstances:

3.1 MANDATORY COMMERCIAL LICENSE

A Commercial License is required if:

  (a) REVENUE THRESHOLD: You are a For-Profit Agricultural Enterprise with
      Annual Revenue exceeding One Million United States Dollars
      (USD $1,000,000) or equivalent in local currency; OR

  (b) PROPRIETARY DERIVATIVES: You wish to create Derivative Works that
      are not licensed under AGPL-3.0; OR

  (c) SAAS WITHOUT SOURCE DISCLOSURE: You wish to offer the Software as a
      Network Use service without disclosing Your source code; OR

  (d) WHITE-LABELING: You wish to rebrand, white-label, or remove
      attribution from the Software; OR

  (e) OEM/EMBEDDED USE: You wish to embed the Software in proprietary
      products distributed to third parties.

3.2 COMMERCIAL LICENSE EXEMPTIONS

The following are EXEMPT from Commercial License requirements, even if
they would otherwise qualify under Section 3.1:

  (a) Government agencies and publicly-funded breeding programs;

  (b) CGIAR centers and their affiliated programs;

  (c) Registered non-profit organizations and NGOs;

  (d) Educational institutions for teaching and research;

  (e) Farmer cooperatives and farmer producer organizations;

  (f) For-Profit Agricultural Enterprises headquartered in countries
      classified as "Low Income" or "Lower Middle Income" by the
      World Bank, provided Annual Revenue does not exceed Ten Million
      United States Dollars (USD $10,000,000).

3.3 EVALUATION PERIOD

Commercial entities may evaluate the Software for up to ninety (90) days
without a Commercial License. Evaluation use must be limited to internal
testing and assessment and may not include production deployment or
Network Use.

3.4 OBTAINING A COMMERCIAL LICENSE

To obtain a Commercial License, contact:

  Email: denishdholaria@gmail.com
  Subject: "Bijmantra Commercial License Inquiry"

Commercial License terms, including fees, are set forth in
COMMERCIAL_LICENSE.md and are subject to negotiation based on use case,
organization size, and other factors.

================================================================================
                    SECTION 4: ETHICAL USE RESTRICTIONS
================================================================================

4.1 PROHIBITED USES

ALL use of the Software, whether under the Open Source License or a
Commercial License, is subject to the Ethical Use Policy set forth in
ETHICAL_USE_POLICY.md, which is incorporated herein by reference.

The Software may NOT be used, directly or indirectly, in connection with:

  (a) GENETIC USE RESTRICTION TECHNOLOGIES (GURTs): Any technology that
      restricts the use of genetic material, including but not limited to
      technologies that render seeds or plant genetic material sterile,
      non-viable, or dependent on proprietary chemical inducers.

  (b) TERMINATOR TECHNOLOGY: Any technology designed to produce sterile
      seeds or prevent farmers from saving, replanting, or sharing seeds.

  (c) TRAITOR TECHNOLOGY: Any technology requiring application of
      proprietary chemicals to activate, maintain, or express genetic
      traits in plants.

  (d) SEED TERMINATION: Any method, technology, or practice designed to
      prevent seeds from being saved, replanted, shared, or used for
      subsequent generations.

4.2 AUTOMATIC TERMINATION

Any use of the Software in violation of Section 4.1 results in IMMEDIATE
and AUTOMATIC termination of all license rights, including any Commercial
License, without notice and without opportunity to cure.

4.3 CERTIFICATION

By using the Software, You certify that:

  (a) You are not currently engaged in developing, producing, or deploying
      any technology described in Section 4.1;

  (b) You will not use the Software or any Derivative Work in connection
      with any technology described in Section 4.1;

  (c) You will not transfer, license, or otherwise make the Software
      available to any party that You know or have reason to believe is
      engaged in activities described in Section 4.1.

